# Security

Apply when working on auth, admin routes, or user input.

## Auth

- Client: JWT in `localStorage`, Bearer header via `client/src/api/axiosConfig.js`
- Server: JWT in `adminController.js`, verified by `server/src/middleware/auth.js`
- Admin guard is client-side only — server does not enforce role checks yet

## Input

- DOMPurify on rendered HTML (client)
- Validators in `server/src/validators/` (server)
- Preserve rate limiters on login, comments, and AI endpoints

## Secrets

- Never commit `.env` files
- No passwords or tokens in source code or Cursor rules
- Credentials belong in `.env.example` / README only

## Do Not

- Assume server enforces admin role
- Remove Helmet, CORS, or rate limiters without replacement
